40:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"The financial case is compelling. A single emergency plumbing callout at 2am averages £280 in callout fees plus £400–£800 in follow-up work. A locksmith attending a midnight lockout charges £150–£250 for the emergency callout. A heating engineer responding to a Sunday boiler failure can invoice £200–£350 for the callout plus £500–£1,200 for replacement parts and labour. At whoza.ai's entry price of £59/month, capturing just one emergency job every two months generates a 340% return on investment."}]
41:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 text-sm mb-3","children":"Boiler failures in winter are health hazards, especially for elderly or vulnerable households. No heating in sub-zero temperatures is treated as an emergency. Callout: £150–£300. Boiler replacement: £800–£2,500."}]
